  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: center">Fig 9: Easy manipulation of colormaps by just changing color shades. (<a href="https://gist.github.com/rohitsuratekar/61bf26d878dddbbcde628ae696d010d6">Full Code</a>)</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>You can adjust the gradient in your colormap by adjusting color order and shades provided during the colormap generation.</p>

<div class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">c1</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">ibm</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">green</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">shade</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">ibm</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">green</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">shade</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">30</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">ibm</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">green</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">shade</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">)]</span>
<span class="n">c2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">ibm</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">green</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">shade</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">ibm</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">green</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">shade</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">50</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">ibm</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">green</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">shade</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">)]</span>
<span class="n">c3</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">ibm</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">green</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">shade</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">ibm</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">green</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">shade</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">70</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">ibm</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">green</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">shade</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">)]</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th style="text-align: center"><a name="fig10"></a><img src="/assets/article_images/2019-06-17-matplotlib-secret-colors/shade_shift.png" alt="" /></th>
